itemdescription_propertiesownerid: The user resource identifier of the subscription owner. The value is a valid relative URL in the format of /users/{userId} where {userId} is a user identifier.
itemdescription_propertiesdisplayname: The name of the subscription, or null if the subscription has no name.
itemdescription_propertiesprimarykey: Subscription primary key. This property will not be filled on 'GET' operations! Use '/listSecrets' POST request to get the value.
itemdescription_propertiessecondarykey: Subscription secondary key. This property will not be filled on 'GET' operations! Use '/listSecrets' POST request to get the value.
itemdescription_propertiesstate: Subscription state. Possible states are * active – the subscription is active, * suspended – the subscription is blocked, and the subscriber cannot call any APIs of the product, * submitted – the subscription request has been made by the developer, but has not yet been approved or rejected, * rejected – the subscription request has been denied by an administrator, * cancelled – the subscription has been cancelled by the developer or administrator, * expired – the subscription reached its expiration date and was deactivated.
itemdescription_propertiescreateddate: Subscription creation date. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.
itemdescription_propertiesstartdate: Subscription activation date. The setting is for audit purposes only and the subscription is not automatically activated. The subscription lifecycle can be managed by using the `state` property. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.
itemdescription_propertiesexpirationdate: Subscription expiration date. The setting is for audit purposes only and the subscription is not automatically expired. The subscription lifecycle can be managed by using the `state` property. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.
itemdescription_propertiesenddate: Date when subscription was cancelled or expired. The setting is for audit purposes only and the subscription is not automatically cancelled. The subscription lifecycle can be managed by using the `state` property. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.
itemdescription_propertiesnotificationda: Upcoming subscription expiration notification date. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.
itemdescription_propertiesstatecomment: Optional subscription comment added by an administrator when the state is changed to the 'rejected'.
